  "local_port": 50072,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm doing my first pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3. What stats do I need to build on to be most effective?",
  "response": "When creating a pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3, you'll want to focus on several key stats to maximize your effectiveness with pyromancy spells, as well as complement your build with appropriate weapons and armor. Here are the primary stats you should focus on:\n\n1. **Intelligence and Faith**: Pyromancy scales with both Intelligence and Faith. To deal significant damage with your pyromancies, you'll want to invest equally in both of these stats. Aim to have them at around 40 each for optimal damage output, as pyromancy scaling has diminishing returns beyond that point.\n\n2. **Attunement**: This stat increases your Focus Points (FP) and the number of attunement slots for equipping more spells. A higher Attunement stat is crucial for casting more spells in succession and having a variety of pyromancies at your disposal. Aim for at least 24 Attunement to have a decent amount of FP and multiple attunement slots.\n\n3. **Vigor**: Vigor increases your health pool, which is essential for survival, especially since pyromancers can be somewhat vulnerable in close combat. Having around 27-30 Vigor is a good balance between offense and resilience.\n\n4. **Endurance**: While not as critical as other stats, having a moderate level of Endurance will help maintain your stamina for dodging and melee attacks. Aim for around 20 Endurance to ensure you have enough stamina for casting and evasive maneuvers.\n\n5. **Dexterity and Strength**: These are less important for a pure pyromancer, but if you plan to use melee weapons alongside your pyromancies, you may need to invest a little in these stats depending on your weapon of choice.\n\nIn addition to stats, consider the following for your pyromancer build:\n\n- **Equipment**: Use the Pyromancy Flame to cast your spells. You may also consider melee weapons that require low stat investments, such as a dagger or a longsword, to complement your spellcasting.\n  \n- **Armor**: Focus on lighter armor sets to maintain mobility, as you'll want to dodge frequently. Consider sets like the Black Leather Armor, Fire Keeper Set, or any set that provides decent protection without heavily burdening you.\n\n- **Rings**: Equip rings that boost your spellcasting abilities and survival. Some recommended rings are the Sage Ring (increases casting speed), Great Swamp Ring, Witch's Ring (both boost pyromancy damage), and the Cloranthy Ring (enhances stamina recovery).\n\nBy focusing on these stats and equipment choices, you'll be well on your way to creating an effective and powerful pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3.",
